    {
      "id": "PopularPost303746",
      "post_content": "A ridiculously overpowered land made even more powerful because of its non-legendary status and its ability to pull any creature directly from graveyard to battlefield. Seven plains is not hard to get, especially given dual lands that serve as both plains and forest ([Savannah](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Savannah) and [Temple Garden](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Temple Garden)). Splashing green makes for easy ramp, though mono-white decks will find it easy as well ([Gift of Estates](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gift of Estates ) , [Tithe](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tithe)) to hit seven plains status, at which point creature removal requires either land destruction, graveyard hosing, or creature exiling. It's as overpowered as [Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle ) . [Wake of Destruction](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wake of Destruction) and [Flashfires](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flashfires) are quite effective here.",
      "posted_by": "igniteice",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost303746\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">A ridiculously overpowered land made even more powerful because of its non-legendary status and its ability to pull any creature directly from graveyard to battlefield. Seven plains is not hard to get, especially given dual lands that serve as both plains and forest (<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Savannah\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Savannah\">Savannah</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Temple Garden\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Temple Garden\">Temple Garden</a>). Splashing green makes for easy ramp, though mono-white decks will find it easy as well (<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Gift of Estates \" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gift of Estates \">Gift of Estates </a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tithe\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tithe\">Tithe</a>) to hit seven plains status, at which point creature removal requires either land destruction, graveyard hosing, or creature exiling. It's as overpowered as <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle \" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle \">Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle </a>. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Wake of Destruction\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wake of Destruction\">Wake of Destruction</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Flashfires\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flashfires\">Flashfires</a> are quite effective here.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubCont