    {
      "id": "PopularPost161540",
      "post_content": "I don't know why so many people seem to be hating on this. I use this in a Paradox Haze deck and it is just awesome. A [Paradox Haze](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Paradox Haze) or two will give you two or three upkeeps, and with two or three of these on the table lets you bring 4-9 creatures back to play each turn. [Endless Horizons](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Endless Horizons) will throw down an extra two/three planes each turn, plus a [Chronozoa](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chronozoa) on the table. I used the example with 2 hazes because that means every turn the chronozoa will vanish, putting two on the table. During your upkeep, you can pull three from the graveyard, next turn, you have 6 more...I assure you it gets ridiculus quite quickly. If you really are hurting, throw out a [Savor the Moment](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Savor the Moment) for a total of 6 upkeeps for three mana. Even further, you can use either [Rising Waters](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rising Waters) or [Hokori, Dust Drinker](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hokori, Dust Drinker) for some massive mana advantage. You are putting more mana on the table ever... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "CallmeMerry",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost161540\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_post\">I don't know why so many people seem to be hating on this.  I use this in a Paradox Haze deck and it is just awesome.  A <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Paradox Haze\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Paradox Haze\">Paradox Haze</a> or two will give you two or three upkeeps, and with two or three of these on the table lets you bring 4-9 creatures back to play each turn.  <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Endless Horizons\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Endless Horizons\">Endless Horizons</a> will throw down an extra two/three planes each turn, plus a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Chronozoa\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chronozoa\">Chronozoa</a> on the table.  I used the example with 2 hazes because that means every turn the chronozoa will vanish, putting two on the table.  During your upkeep, you can pull three from the graveyard, next turn, you have 6 more...I assure you it gets ridiculus quite quickly.  If you really are hurting, throw out a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Savor the Moment\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Savor the Moment\">Savor the Moment</a> for a total of 6 upkeeps for three mana.  Even further, you can use either <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Rising Waters\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rising Waters\">Rising Waters</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Hokori, Dust Drinker\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hokori, Dust Drinker\">Hokori, Dust Drinker</a> for some massive mana advantage.  You are putting more mana on the table ever... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 161540)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '161540'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy52441\">CallmeMerry</span>\r\n                                (5/17/2011 12:58:03 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
